 To bring out the industrialisation that Africa needs, countries on the continent need to harmonise their policies. In particular credit policies need to be revised. That’s according to Ayodele Odusola, Chief Economist and the Head of Strategy at the UNDP’s Regional Bureau for Africa. CNBC Africa’s Kenneth Igbomor caught up with him recently and he addressed the policies that need to be tweaked for Africa to achieve the outcomes it desires. https://www.cnbcafrica.com/videos/